amarantin command reference
===========================

Overview
--------
Repository operating notes for agents and contributors.

Purpose
-------
This repo is a small C++17 / ROOT project for building persistent ROOT-based
sample containers and derived dataset / event-list artifacts.

Primary code paths
------------------
io/              Core I/O library
ana/             Analysis-side helpers and event-list construction
syst/            Systematics cache construction
plot/            Plotting library
fit/             Signal-strength fitting library
app/             Command-line tools
tools/           Helper scripts
samples-dag.mk   Higher-level sample workflow
datasets.mk      Sample-list declarations consumed by samples-dag.mk

Primary executables
-------------------
  * build/bin/mk_sample
  * build/bin/mk_dataset
  * build/bin/mk_eventlist
  * build/bin/mk_dist
  * build/bin/mk_xsec_fit

Canonical build path
--------------------
Treat CMake as the source of truth. Prefer out-of-source builds.

  cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
  cmake --build build --parallel

Additional scratch build trees
------------------------------
Keep extra local build trees under the hidden `.build/` parent instead of
spilling `build-*` and `cmake-build-*` directories into the repo root.

  tools/configure-build host
  cmake --build .build/host --parallel

Environment setup
-----------------
GPVM / Fermilab container
  source ./.container.sh
  source ./.setup.sh

Docker
  docker build -t amarantin-dev .
  docker run --rm -it -v "$PWD":/work -w /work amarantin-dev bash

Core build commands
-------------------
Configure
  cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release

Build everything
